EmailTemplate.description: Email to send to a worker when they submit a case item to Merit Review case
EmailTemplate.name: Worker Application Submitted Worker Email
EmailTemplate.subject: Application for merit review by authority (Case Number {CaseNumber})
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Contact.Name},
We acknowledge receipt of your application for merit review received by the Merit Review Service on {dateTimeStamp}, and it is awaiting assignment to one of our team members.
Once the application has been reviewed, the Insurer will be requested to lodge a completed ‘Work capacity – reply to an application for merit review by the authority’ form as quickly as possible and preferably within 7 days.
Please note that this acknowledgment is not confirmation that the Authority has jurisdiction to review the work capacity decision/s of the Insurer. This is a decision that will be made prior to the review being undertaken, and, in the event that the application is not accepted, both parties will be advised in writing in due course.
Please refer to the attached information sheet which will assist you in understanding the merit review process.
If you need assistance please do not hesitate to contact us via email mrs@sira.nsw.gov.au or call us on 02 9284 2284.
Yours sincerely
Merit Review Service
